<br>
I understand there were 4 chanters in attendance and at least one expressed to me their interest in looting what I was there to loot.  I hope there are no hard feelings regarding it, but I lead this raid to get the drop.  I've reviewed the raid planning and I believe the loot policy was clear.<br>
<br>
For any chanter still looking to get the head, I'm more than happy to help.<br>
<br>
BBSCO Epic Loot Policy Summary which I dont think differs from most guilds (maybe slightly):<br>
If you lead the raid and state that there is reserved loot, you get it. If you are not leading the raid, you roll with the others.<br>
<br>
Here are the snipets<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Post on 1/24/03</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
As the BBSco loot policy states, I will get the loot I am going for. We must discuss as a guild my intention of taking either the Warrior loot or the Chanter loot pending spawns. Both chars will be in attendance and contributing.<br>
All other loot including epic is to be rolled upon based on BBSco loot policy.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Post by Bregalad on 1/26/03</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Guess Sele has first dibs on head of serpent (one of 5 items needed by Bregalad to finish epic) but this is also my primary (and pretty much only) target in Fear.<br>
<br>
Post on 1/27/03<br>
Epic loot is handled the same with a couple additions:<br>
It's still need before greed and the same roll, however when someone from BBSco leads a raid for their epic piece, they are following BBSco policies and it is considered a blackburrow raid. They get the item they are looking for. The person seeking the epic must be leading the raid.<br>
In this case I am leading this raid and have dibs on the Ball of Everliving Golem. After discussing with BBSco leads, they have agreed that if the Golems are not up, Sele may have dibs on the Head Of The Serpent. All other loot will be &quot;Need Before Greed/On your way to epic&quot; roll. Note the &quot;on your way to epic&quot; which means this should not be your first step on your epic quest.<br>
<br>
On a side note, if Pow does get the Ball of EG, I would be eligable to roll for the Head, but WILL NOT roll. My goal is only to acheive one item.<br>
<br>
P<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>ost on 1/28/03</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
This post explains non reserved loot but isn’t an official BBSco policy. Our policy is slightly different, but close.<br>
Let's not get nasty guys! The way it works (from what I've seen anyway) is that the people closest to that step in their epic have dibs on the drop.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Post on 1/29/03 I explained the non reserved loot in more detail</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
To explain the &quot;on your way to epic&quot; policy I mentioned in my loot policy post.<br>
<br>
Not all epics are exactly sequential. In some cases you may gather components here and there not in any order. I am unsure of the Shamen epic quest which was in question. <br>
<br>
Our policy is that all who have started their epic and are actively pursuing the epic have a chance to roll for the loot. Example: Pow may be 75% with Ava at 25% through the warrior epic. Both would have a chance to roll for a warrior item if neither of us lead the raid. <br>
<br>
If our loot manager Miggichic recognized that Ava made that 25% progress only by picking up ground drops, Miggi can ask that Ava step down from the roll. Miggi would not ask Ava to step down if she had completed sub quests and fought mobs to obtain that 25%. Effort is everything.<br>
<br>
It is up to Pow and Ava to decide weather or not to roll. If Ava's fridged heart melts as it usually does around Powpow, she would likely give up her chance to roll for Powpow.<br>
<br>
So we leave it up to those eligable to decide if they will roll or not. With Docat being close to his epic I encourage other Shaman who aren't close to finishing to allow Docat to take the roll. If there are shaman who are close, we say they are eligable to roll.<br>
<br>
I hope this clears it up for those with concerns. I didn't ninja or take the loot unfairly in my opinion.  I spent a lot of time preparing us for this raid and woul stand behind anyone else leading and planning a raid for a specific item even if I were further on the quest. All because they planned it.<br>
<br>
And for those who are further on their epic know, there are a lot of long long waits on the chanter epic and before I wait, I want to get some of the uber kills taken care of rather than waste my time. Things are coming along well.<br>
<br>
